      • track

        public void track(TelemetryData telemetry)
        Sends information about any object that extend TelemetryData interface to Application Insights. For most use-cases, the other tracking methods will be sufficient. Providing this generic method for very specific uses.
        Parameters:
        telemetry - an object that extends TelemetryData

      • trackEvent

        Sends information about an event to Application Insights.
        Parameters:

        properties - Custom properties associated with the event. Note: values set here will supersede values set in ApplicationInsights.setCommonProperties(java.util.Map<java.lang.String, java.lang.String>).

      • trackMetric

        public void trackMetric(java.lang.String name,
                        double value)
        Sends information about an aggregated metric to Application Insights. Note: all data sent via this method will be aggregated. To log non-aggregated data use trackEvent(String, Map, Map) with measurements.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the metric
        value - The value of the metric

      • trackManagedException

        public void trackManagedException(java.lang.String type,
                                  java.lang.String message,
                                  java.lang.String stacktrace,
                                  boolean handled)
        Sends unhandled Exception to Application Insights. This method should be called from your Xamarin code to send the C# stacktrace to ApplicationInsights and ignore the report created by ExceptionTracking.
        Parameters:
        type - the exception type
        message - the exception message
        stacktrace - the stacktrace for the exception
        handled - a flag which determines if the exception was handled or not
